---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Mixing" active="mixing">
  <div class="container">

    <section class="page-header">
      <h3>Analog Console</h3>
      <h1>Mixing</h1>
      <p>The Tascam Model 12 receives processed stems from the Wing via matrices. Real faders, analog EQ, compression. Every mix pass captured on tracks 11/12.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="vu-bar"></div>

    <section>
      <h3>Mix Signal Flow</h3>
      <div class="signal-flow mt-sm">
<span class="comment">  // sources</span>
  <span class="node">Logic</span> <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> Wing Ch25-32 (tape returns) + Ch9-12 (session players)
  <span class="arrow">|</span>
<span class="comment">  // processing</span>
  Wing adds: amp sims (Bus 10/11), reverb (Bus 3), vocal doubler (MX2), bass octaver (MX6)
  <span class="arrow">|</span>
<span class="comment">  // routing</span>
  Wing Matrices MX2-MX8 <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> USB 33-42 <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> Loopback <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> <span class="node">Model 12 Ch 1-10</span>
  <span class="arrow">|</span>
<span class="comment">  // mixing</span>
  <span class="gear">Model 12</span>: faders, EQ, compression, AUX sends
  <span class="arrow">|</span>
  Tracks 11/12: stereo mixdown (always recording)
  <span class="arrow">|</span>
<span class="comment">  // monitoring</span>
  Model 12 Main Out <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> USB <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> Loopback <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> <span class="node">Wing Ch7</span> (solo to hear mix)</div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Mix Matrices</h3>
      <p class="mt-sm">Permanent routing layer. Wire once, change sources per project. Each matrix feeds a dedicated USB output to a Model 12 channel.</p>
      <table class="mt-md">
        <tr><th>Matrix</th><th>Name</th><th>USB Out</th><th>M12 Ch</th><th>Source</th><th>Post-Insert</th></tr>
        <tr><td>MX2</td><td>Mix Vocal</td><td>33</td><td>1</td><td>Ch25 + Ch17 (live)</td><td>FX3 DOUBLE/THICK</td></tr>
        <tr><td>MX3</td><td>Mix Rhythm</td><td>34</td><td>2</td><td>Bus 10 (FX7 RACKAMP)</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><td>MX4</td><td>Mix Lead</td><td>35</td><td>3</td><td>Bus 11 (FX12 ANGEL)</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><td>MX5</td><td>Mix Overdub</td><td>36</td><td>4</td><td>Per project</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><td>MX6</td><td>Mix Bass</td><td>37</td><td>5</td><td>Ch9 (Logic bass)</td><td>FX4 SUB/MID</td></tr>
        <tr><td>MX7</td><td>Mix Drums</td><td>39-40</td><td>7/8</td><td>Ch12 (Logic drums)</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><td>MX8</td><td>Mix Piano</td><td>41-42</td><td>9/10</td><td>Ch11 (Logic piano)</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Tape Saturation &mdash; AUX 1 Loop</h3>
      <div class="signal-flow mt-sm">
<span class="comment">  // parallel tape saturation via Model 12 AUX 1 send/return</span>

  <span class="gear">Model 12 AUX 1 Out</span> (pre-fader, per-channel knob)
  <span class="arrow">|</span> TRS &rarr; XLR cable (direct, no patchbay)
  <span class="arrow">|</span>
  <span class="node">Wing LCL 3</span> (gain 10dB, phantom OFF)
  <span class="arrow">|</span>
  <span class="node">Ch33 Tape Send</span>
  <span class="arrow">|</span> pre-insert: <span class="gear">FX13 TAPE</span> (drive 10, speed 30)
  <span class="arrow">|</span> post-insert: <span class="gear">FX6 TAPE-DL</span> (flutter 55, no delay feedback)
  <span class="arrow">|</span>
  USR/3 (POST tap) <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> USB 38 <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> Loopback <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> <span class="node">Model 12 Ch 6</span>

<span class="comment">  // WARNING: do NOT send drums to AUX 1</span>
<span class="comment">  // round-trip latency causes audible slapback on transients</span></div>

      <div class="grid-2 mt-md">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">How It Works</span>
          <h4>Parallel Processing</h4>
          <p>The dry signal goes through the Model 12's main bus. AUX 1 sends a copy through the Wing's TAPE effects and returns on Ch 6. Blend with the Ch 6 fader. AUX 1 knobs control per-channel send amount.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">Limitation</span>
          <h4>Mono Sum + Latency</h4>
          <p>AUX 1 is mono &mdash; collapses stereo to center. The USB round-trip adds a few ms of delay, audible on drums as slapback. Keep AUX 1 down on percussive material.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Model 12 Channel Map</h3>
      <table class="mt-sm">
        <tr><th>M12 Ch</th><th>Source</th><th>Content</th><th>AUX 1 (Tape)</th><th>AUX 2 (FX)</th></tr>
        <tr><td>1</td><td>MX2 / USB 33</td><td>Vocal</td><td>To taste</td><td>Reverb</td></tr>
        <tr><td>2</td><td>MX3 / USB 34</td><td>Rhythm Guitar</td><td>To taste</td><td>Reverb</td></tr>
        <tr><td>3</td><td>MX4 / USB 35</td><td>Lead Guitar</td><td>To taste</td><td>Reverb</td></tr>
        <tr><td>4</td><td>MX5 / USB 36</td><td>Overdub</td><td>Per project</td><td>Per project</td></tr>
        <tr><td>5</td><td>MX6 / USB 37</td><td>Bass</td><td>To taste</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><td>6</td><td>USR/3 / USB 38</td><td>Tape Return</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><td>7/8</td><td>MX7 / USB 39-40</td><td>Drums</td><td>OFF</td><td>To taste</td></tr>
        <tr><td>9/10</td><td>MX8 / USB 41-42</td><td>Piano/Synth</td><td>To taste</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><td>11/12</td><td>Internal</td><td>Stereo Mixdown</td><td colspan="2">Always recording</td></tr>
      </table>
    </section>

  </div>
</Base>
